# Security

Implements: ADR-010. WHY: `docs/architecture/adr-010-security.md`. RBAC how-to → `permissions.mdc`. Tenant schema prep → `database.mdc` / `migration.mdc`.

## Secure defaults

- New integrations/features **disabled** until configured
- New endpoints require authentication + Policy/ability check by default
- Admin/API middleware stacks include `auth`, module gates, and (post-Phase-28) tenant context — skipping any needs a documented reason (e.g. signature-verified webhooks)

## Authorization

- Server-side Policies only as the real boundary (`permissions.mdc`)
- Frontend `useCan()` is UX only
- Post-Phase-28: `withoutGlobalScope(TenantScope::class)` is a security-sensitive escape hatch — treat like `sudo`; never on tenant-reachable paths

## Validation & injection

- All input through FormRequests / validated APIs
- Eloquent / query builder parameter binding only — no string-concatenated SQL
- Authorize before acting; validate before trusting

## Secrets & encryption

- Sensitive columns: Laravel encrypted casts — not ad hoc crypto
- Credentials in `.env` or encrypted settings tables — never hardcoded, never logged
- Do not commit `.env` or real secrets; document required keys in `CLAUDE.md`

## Rate limiting & auth abuse

- Auth-sensitive routes (login, PIN): rate limit; POS PIN lockout precedent (5 attempts → 15 min)
- Public API: per-token quotas in addition to IP limits (`api.mdc`)
- Webhook receivers: verify signature before processing

## Tenant isolation

- Pre-Phase-28: nullable `tenant_id` prep only — no fake isolation logic
- After Phase 28/29: cross-tenant read/write is a **security incident**, not a normal data bug

## OWASP quick check (new risky code)

| Risk | Do |
| :--- | :--- |
| Access control | Policy + server enforce; tenant scope when live |
| Crypto | Encrypted casts; TLS non-local; no secrets in logs |
| Injection | Bound queries + FormRequests |
| Misconfig | Secure defaults; no committed secrets |
| Auth failures | Session/Sanctum correctly; PIN lockout for secrets |
| Integrity | Audit trail; webhook signatures |
| SSRF | No user-controlled outbound URLs without allow-list |

Touching auth, uploads, outbound HTTP, or raw SQL → review against this table before merge.

## Payments / PCI posture

- Prefer gateway hosted fields / tokenization — do not pull raw card data into RetailPulse request paths
